data.title: Massive tree falls on top of car on Upper East Side after rain, high winds impact NYC
data.meta_description: A massive tree fell on top of a car in Manhattan.
data.text:
UPPER EAST SIDE, Manhattan (WABC) -- A massive tree fell on top of a car in Manhattan on Saturday.

It happened at 1120 Fifth Ave. between East 93rd and 94th Street.

The tree blocked part of Fifth Avenue before the city's Department of Parks & Recreation removed it.

No injuries were reported.

The NYC Parks Dept. said they received 31 service requests for trees down, which comes after blustery and rainy conditions impacts parts of the Tri-State on Saturday.

Heavy rain and high winds in the Tri-State Area created an absolute mess.
